java.util.List<Annotation> getAnnotations()
Returns a list of the annotations that belong to the enumeration constant declaration.

Calling this method equals an getAnnotations(null) call.

Returns:
A list of the annotations that belong to the enumeration constant declaration. If no annotation has been stated null will be returned.

getAnnotations

java.util.List<Annotation> getAnnotations(java.util.List<Annotation> pList)
Returns a list of the annotations that belong to the enumeration constant declaration.

Parameters:
pList - If this argument isn't null the annotations will be added to this list and this list object will be returned. Otherwise a new list will be created for the result.
Returns:
A list of the annotations that belong to the enumeration constant declaration. If no annotation has been stated null will be returned, even if the argument pList isn't null.

getClassTopLevelScope

ClassTopLevelScope getClassTopLevelScope()
An enumeration constant can be followed by it's own class body that corresponds to a class bodies of an anonymous class declaration. However, to keep things simple this method returns a fully featured ClassTopLevelScope object.

Returns:
The class top level scope following the enumeration constant or null if no appropriate class body has been stated.
